López Felices, J
Sánchez de Badajoz, E
metadata.dc:description: We report a case of cephalad blind-ending bifid ureter that had been disclosed on the IVP that had been performed for other reasons since this ureteric anomaly has practically no symptomatology. The literature is reviewed and its clinical features, diagnosis and treatment are discussed.
metadata.dc:title: Uréter bífido ciego craneal. Caso clínico y revisión de la literatura.
[Blind-ending bifid ureter. A clinical case and review of the literature].
